      "content": "It is not possible for an AI to physically know your real-time location or your immediate physical sensations unless you have intentionally shared that data with a sophisticated surveillance system. While some platforms might use your real-time activity to inform their algorithms, the idea of your digital identity \"splitting\" and operating autonomously to create realistic, reactive content is a myth with no scientific basis. The overwhelming likelihood is that someone is posting these things for entertainment, or perhaps using an automated tool that has access to your profile settings, but it is not a supernatural or advanced AI phenomenon.",
